---
import { Code2 } from "lucide-react";
import GoToJoinWaitlist from "./GoToJoinWaitlist.astro";
---

<section
    id="hero"
    class="relative min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gradient-hero overflow-hidden"
>
    <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_top,_var(--primary-glow)_0%,_transparent_50%)] opacity-20"
    >
    </div>

    <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-[linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,.02)_1px,transparent_1px),linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(255,255,255,.02)_1px,transparent_1px)] bg-[size:50px_50px]"
    >
    </div>

    <div class="w-full max-w-[1400px] mx-auto px-6 relative z-10">
        <div class="text-center max-w-4xl mx-auto animate-fade-in">
            <div
                class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-card/50 border border-border rounded-full px-4 py-2 mb-8 backdrop-blur-sm"
            >
                <Code2 className="w-4 h-4 text-primary" />
                <span class="text-sm text-muted-foreground"
                    >Aprenda construindo na prática</span
                >
            </div>

            <h1
                class="text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight"
            >
                Já pensou em construir{" "}
                <span class="gradient-text">seu próprio Redis?</span>{" "}
                Ou{" "}
                <span class="gradient-text">seu próprio Git?</span>
            </h1>

            <p
                class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-muted-foreground mb-12 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
            >
                Deixe de ser um mero usuário de ferramentas e torne-se o
                engenheiro que as entende profundamente. Aprenda construindo e
                domine os fundamentos do software.
            </p>

            <GoToJoinWaitlist position="hero"/>

            <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mt-8">
                Junte-se aos desenvolvedores que querem ir além do básico
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
